name.text: Using division to find reciprocal of the given numbers

questiontext.text:
Using division, find the reciprocal of each of the following numbers.
Enter answers as fractions in simplest form.

  1. \({@a@}\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]
  2. \({@b@}\) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]]
  3. \({@c@}\) [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]]
  4. \({@d@}\) [[input:ans4]] [[validation:ans4]]
  5. \({@e@}\) [[input:ans5]] [[validation:ans5]]
  6. \({@f@}\) [[input:ans6]] [[validation:ans6]]

[[feedback:prt1]] [[feedback:prt2]] [[feedback:prt3]] [[feedback:prt4]] [[feedback:prt5]] [[feedback:prt6]]

generalfeedback.text:
Worked Solution

Using division to find the reciprocal of a real number is dividing 1 by the number (1 รท number)

Therefore, the reciprocal of the given numbers are:

a)

\(\begin{align} {@a@} =& 1 \div {@a@}\\ =& {@ta1@} \end{align}\)


b)

\(\begin{align} {@b@} =& 1 \div {@b@}\\ =& {@ta2@} \end{align}\)


c)

\(\begin{align}{@c@} =& 1 \div {@c@}\\ =& {@ta3@} \end{align}\)


d)

\(\begin{align}{@d@} =& 1 \div {@d@}\\ =& {@ta4@} \end{align}\)


e)

\(\begin{align}{@e@} =& 1 \div {@e@}\\ =& {@ta5@} \end{align}\)


f)

\(\begin{align}{@f@} =& 1 \div {@f@}\\ =& {@ta6@} \end{align}\)
